The paper discusses the use of ontologies in information extraction, which is a common topic in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also focuses on the interpretation of extracted information, which is a key aspect of information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of domain models and knowledge in the extraction process suggests a connection to databases (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG).
